[SN]TITLE[SN]
Cork stabbing: Paul Horgan charged with murdering his mother Marian

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has appeared in court charged with murdering his mother at their family home in the Republic of Ireland.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Paul Horgan was arrested after his 60-year-old mother, Marian Horgan, was stabbed at their house in Murmont Avenue, Cork, on Monday.
Cork District Court was told the 25-year-old student made no reply when police charged him with the murder.
The judge ordered him to undergo psychiatric assessment and remanded him into custody until next Tuesday.
